title: Proposal to Update Lottery Mechanics
body:
We're proposing to increase in the total number of digits used in the lottery tickets. 

We hope that increasing the digits and with it reducing the chance of winning the number of high-value pots will greatly increase, leading to larger burns and greater participation overall.

Currently, 10 digits are used in the lottery tickets (1-10) and the odds of getting 4 numbers in the correct order in a row gives you a 1/10000 chance of winning. 

Some options for proposed digit increases are below for you to vote on.
choices: Increase to 11 digits - 1/14641 chance to win jackpot
Increase to 12 digits - 1/20736 chance to win jackpot
Increase to 13 digits - 1/28561 chance to win jackpot
Increase to 14 digits - 1/38416 chance to win jackpot
